post_text: Football Tickets for the Homecoming Game vs Ranger will go on sale Monday Sept. 14th for Football, Band , & Cheer Parents from 11am-1pm at the Depot. post_text:
Itasca ISD has been notified that an individual participating in the High School Boys Strength and Conditioning program this morning at Itasca High School has been exposed to COVID-19. Due to this exposure the Athletic Department has suspended the Summer Workout Program for the High School Boys ONLY until July 27th, 2020.

Out of an abundance of caution the district has notified all parents of athletes that may have come into contact with that athlete. If you did not receive a phone call this afternoon, your child was not in direct contact with this individual.

As always, we will continue to screen students daily and practice health and safety procedures as outlined by the U.I.L., TEA, etc. In effect, the High School Girls, Middle School Girls and Middle School Boys Summer Program will proceed as scheduled.
text:
Itasca ISD has been notified that an individual participating in the High School Boys Strength and Conditioning program this morning at Itasca High School has been exposed to COVID-19. Due to this exposure the Athletic Department has suspended the Summer Workout Program for the High School Boys ONLY until July 27th, 2020.

Out of an abundance of caution the district has notified all parents of athletes that may have come into contact with that athlete. If you did not receive a phone call this afternoon, your child was not in direct contact with this individual.

As always, we will continue to screen students daily and practice health and safety procedures as outlined by the U.I.L., TEA, etc. In effect, the High School Girls, Middle School Girls and Middle School Boys Summer Program will proceed as scheduled.

Fever or chills
Cough
Shortness of breath or difficulty breathing

Headache
New loss of taste or smell
Sore throat
Congestion or runny nose
Nausea or vomiting
Diarrhea

post_text:
Today is Graduation Day for the Class of 2020! Please remember:
1) There will be no public entry onto school grounds without a ticket
2) Parking opens at 6:15 pm
3) Gates open at 6:30 pm
3) Feel free to bring bottled water (but only bottled water please)
4) Security will be enforced around the entire perimeter
5) Gates close at 7:25 pm
6) Do not bring anything with you into the stadium (flowers, balloons, gifts, horns, signs, etc.)
We need your help to make this a special and memorable experience for our graduates. Don't forget, you can watch the entire ceremony live at https://youtu.be/T-YB7pSqNws , and please check out all other details about the ceremony at https://www.itascaisd.org/article/255970?org=itasca-isd.

Every Athlete must fill out a Medical History Form and return it to Coach Jackson, before you can participate in a sport 2020-2021 school year.

post_text: Congratulations to our Wampus Cat baseball team for defeating Abbott 9-8 to win the 1st Annual Wampus Cat Invitational Baseball tournament on Saturday!
text: Congratulations to our Wampus Cat baseball team for defeating Abbott 9-8 to win the 1st Annual Wampus Cat Invitational Baseball tournament on Saturday!

shared_text:
Wampus Cat Baseball
March 8 at 12:25 AM ¬∑

Down 8-0 in the championship to a team that is a fundamentally sound as it gets, our young men had their character tested and passed. Clawed away inning by inning with big time hits and walks coming from all up and down the lineup. Combined with an outstanding performance in relief by Andrew Arellano, these young men beat Abbott 9-8. Great weekend of baseball, we got better. Now a rematch vs. Abbott on Tuesday for district game #1.

Thanks to all the teams that participated in the Wampus Cat Invitational!

Itasca Isd
